hpnicfVoiceEntityControl.name: hpnicfVoiceEntityControl

revisions.description: The initial version of this MIB file.

hpnicfVoiceEntityControl.description: This MIB file is to provide the definition of voice dial control configuration.

hpnicfVoEntityCreateTable.name: hpnicfVoEntityCreateTable
hpnicfVoEntityCreateTable.description: The table contains the voice entity information that is used to create an ifIndexed row.

hpnicfVoEntityIndex.name: hpnicfVoEntityIndex
hpnicfVoEntityIndex.description: An arbitrary index that uniquely identifies a voice entity.

hpnicfVoEntityType.name: hpnicfVoEntityType
hpnicfVoEntityType.description: Specify the type of voice related encapsulation.

hpnicfVoEntityRowStatus.name: hpnicfVoEntityRowStatus
hpnicfVoEntityRowStatus.description: This object is used to create, delete or modify a row in this table. The hpnicfVoEntityType object should not be modified once the new row has been created.

hpnicfVoEntityCommonConfigTable.name: hpnicfVoEntityCommonConfigTable
hpnicfVoEntityCommonConfigTable.description: This table contains the general voice entity information.

hpnicfVoEntityCfgIndex.name: hpnicfVoEntityCfgIndex
hpnicfVoEntityCfgIndex.description: An arbitrary index that uniquely identifies a voice entity.

hpnicfVoEntityCfgCodec1st.name: hpnicfVoEntityCfgCodec1st
hpnicfVoEntityCfgCodec1st.description: This object indicates the first desirable CODEC of speech of this dial entity.

hpnicfVoEntityCfgCodec2nd.name: hpnicfVoEntityCfgCodec2nd
hpnicfVoEntityCfgCodec2nd.description: This object indicates the second desirable CODEC of speech of this dial entity.

hpnicfVoEntityCfgCodec3rd.name: hpnicfVoEntityCfgCodec3rd
hpnicfVoEntityCfgCodec3rd.description: This object indicates the third desirable CODEC of speech of this dial entity.

hpnicfVoEntityCfgCodec4th.name: hpnicfVoEntityCfgCodec4th
hpnicfVoEntityCfgCodec4th.description: This object indicates the forth desirable CODEC of speech of this dial entity.

hpnicfVoEntityCfgDSCP.name: hpnicfVoEntityCfgDSCP
hpnicfVoEntityCfgDSCP.description: This object indicates the DSCP(Different Service Code Point) value of voice packets.

hpnicfVoEntityCfgVADEnable.name: hpnicfVoEntityCfgVADEnable
hpnicfVoEntityCfgVADEnable.description: This object indicates whether the VAD(Voice Activity Detection) is enabled.

hpnicfVoEntityCfgOutbandMode.name: hpnicfVoEntityCfgOutbandMode
hpnicfVoEntityCfgOutbandMode.description: This object indicates the DTMF(Dual Tone Multi-Frequency) outband type of this dial entity.

hpnicfVoEntityCfgFaxLevel.name: hpnicfVoEntityCfgFaxLevel
hpnicfVoEntityCfgFaxLevel.description: This object indicates the fax level of this dial entity.

hpnicfVoEntityCfgFaxBaudrate.name: hpnicfVoEntityCfgFaxBaudrate
hpnicfVoEntityCfgFaxBaudrate.description: This object indicates the fax baudrate of this dial entity.

hpnicfVoEntityCfgFaxLocalTrainPara.name: hpnicfVoEntityCfgFaxLocalTrainPara
hpnicfVoEntityCfgFaxLocalTrainPara.description: This object indicates the fax local train threshold of this dial entity.

hpnicfVoEntityCfgFaxProtocol.name: hpnicfVoEntityCfgFaxProtocol
hpnicfVoEntityCfgFaxProtocol.description: This object indicates the fax protocol of this dial entity.

hpnicfVoEntityCfgFaxHRPackNum.name: hpnicfVoEntityCfgFaxHRPackNum
hpnicfVoEntityCfgFaxHRPackNum.description: This object indicates the high speed redundancy packet numbers of t38 and standard-t38.

hpnicfVoEntityCfgFaxLRPackNum.name: hpnicfVoEntityCfgFaxLRPackNum
hpnicfVoEntityCfgFaxLRPackNum.description: This object indicates the low speed redundancy packet numbers of t38 and standard-t38.

hpnicfVoEntityCfgFaxSendNSFEnable.name: hpnicfVoEntityCfgFaxSendNSFEnable
hpnicfVoEntityCfgFaxSendNSFEnable.description: This object indicates whether sends NSF(Non-Standard Faculty) to fax of this dial entity.

hpnicfVoEntityCfgFaxTrainMode.name: hpnicfVoEntityCfgFaxTrainMode
hpnicfVoEntityCfgFaxTrainMode.description: This object indicates the fax train mode of this dial entity.

hpnicfVoEntityCfgFaxEcm.name: hpnicfVoEntityCfgFaxEcm
hpnicfVoEntityCfgFaxEcm.description: This object indicates whether the ECM(Error Correct Mode) is enabled.

hpnicfVoEntityCfgPriority.name: hpnicfVoEntityCfgPriority
hpnicfVoEntityCfgPriority.description: This object indicates the priority of this dial entity.

hpnicfVoEntityCfgDescription.name: hpnicfVoEntityCfgDescription
hpnicfVoEntityCfgDescription.description: This object indicates the textual description of this dial entity.

hpnicfVoPOTSEntityConfigTable.name: hpnicfVoPOTSEntityConfigTable
hpnicfVoPOTSEntityConfigTable.description: This table contains the POTS(Public Switched Telephone Network) entity information.

hpnicfVoPOTSEntityConfigIndex.name: hpnicfVoPOTSEntityConfigIndex
hpnicfVoPOTSEntityConfigIndex.description: An arbitrary index that uniquely identifies a voice entity.

hpnicfVoPOTSEntityConfigPrefix.name: hpnicfVoPOTSEntityConfigPrefix
hpnicfVoPOTSEntityConfigPrefix.description: This object indicates the prefix which is added to the called number.

hpnicfVoPOTSEntityConfigSubLine.name: hpnicfVoPOTSEntityConfigSubLine
hpnicfVoPOTSEntityConfigSubLine.description: This object indicates the voice subscriber line of this dial entity.

hpnicfVoPOTSEntityConfigSendNum.name: hpnicfVoPOTSEntityConfigSendNum
hpnicfVoPOTSEntityConfigSendNum.description: This object indicates the digit of phone number to be sent to the destination. 0..31: Number of digits (that are extracted from the end of a number) to be sent, in the range of 0 to 31. It is not greater than the total number of digits of the called number. 65534: Sends all digits of a called number. 65535: Sends a truncated called number.

hpnicfVoVoIPEntityConfigTable.name: hpnicfVoVoIPEntityConfigTable
hpnicfVoVoIPEntityConfigTable.description: This table contains the VoIP entity information.

hpnicfVoVoIPEntityCfgIndex.name: hpnicfVoVoIPEntityCfgIndex
hpnicfVoVoIPEntityCfgIndex.description: An arbitrary index that uniquely identifies a voice entity.

hpnicfVoVoIPEntityCfgTargetType.name: hpnicfVoVoIPEntityCfgTargetType
hpnicfVoVoIPEntityCfgTargetType.description: This object indicates the type of the session target of this entity.

hpnicfVoVoIPEntityCfgTargetAddrType.name: hpnicfVoVoIPEntityCfgTargetAddrType
hpnicfVoVoIPEntityCfgTargetAddrType.description: The IP address type of object hpnicfVoVoIPEntityCfgTargetAddr.

hpnicfVoVoIPEntityCfgTargetAddr.name: hpnicfVoVoIPEntityCfgTargetAddr
hpnicfVoVoIPEntityCfgTargetAddr.description: This object indicates the target IP address.

hpnicfVoEntityNumberTable.name: hpnicfVoEntityNumberTable
hpnicfVoEntityNumberTable.description: The table contains the number management information.

hpnicfVoEntityNumberEntry.name: hpnicfVoEntityNumberEntry
hpnicfVoEntityNumberEntry.description: The entry of hpnicfVoEntityNumberTable. HpnicfVoEntityIndex is used to uniquely identify these numbers registered on the server. The same value of hpnicfVoEntityIndex used in the corresponding HPN-ICFVoEntityCommonConfigTable is used here.

hpnicfVoEntityNumberAuthUser.name: hpnicfVoEntityNumberAuthUser
hpnicfVoEntityNumberAuthUser.description: This object indicates the username of the entity number to authorize.

hpnicfVoEntityNumberPasswordType.name: hpnicfVoEntityNumberPasswordType
hpnicfVoEntityNumberPasswordType.description: This object indicates the password type of the entity number to authorize. The encrypting type of password: 0 : password simple, means password is clean text. 1 : password cipher, means password is encrypted text. default is 65535.

hpnicfVoEntityNumberPassword.name: hpnicfVoEntityNumberPassword
hpnicfVoEntityNumberPassword.description: This object indicates the password of the entity number to authorize.

hpnicfVoEntityNumberStatus.name: hpnicfVoEntityNumberStatus
hpnicfVoEntityNumberStatus.description: This object indicates the current state of the entity number.

hpnicfVoEntityNumberExpires.name: hpnicfVoEntityNumberExpires
hpnicfVoEntityNumberExpires.description: This is the interval time for entity number updating registered message.
